item.title: CVE-2018-10873|2024-08-05T07:46:47.325Z -- %5Bunknown%5D -- spice%3A
item.description: A vulnerability was discovered in SPICE before version 0.14.1 where the generated code used for demarshalling messages lacked sufficient bounds checks. A malicious client or server, after authentication, could send specially crafted messages to its peer which would result in a crash or, potentially, other impacts.
